Caption:
The constant chanting of Sri Radha's name is the very breath of my life. Sri Radha resides in my eyelids and hair, and I have filled the parting of my hair with Shri Radha's name. [1]

Sri Radha resides In my eyes and my speech.
I have woven my braid with the name of Shri Radha. [2]

Shri Radha resides in my dress and scarf, and I have adorned my nose ring with the name of Shri Radha. [3]

Shri Radha guides my every step. I wear the name of Shri Radha as Kinkani (waist-ornament containing multiple bells) on my waist. [4]

Shri Radha is on my right and left, in front and behind me; the essence of Shri Radha's name pervades my every pore. [5]

Shri Radha fills every part of my being, and Sri Radha is always with me. Shri Hita Gopal Das Ji says that even Shri Krishna plays the flute, singing only the name of Shri Radha. [6]

On Wednesday, the Indore Municipal Corporation took possession of seven acres of land known as Karbala Field, following a court ruling in its favor. Previously, the Muslim community used this land for cooling Tazias and holding a fair, but now it fully belongs to the Municipal Corporation. The corporation has also installed a board declaring its ownership of the land.

Mayor Pushya Mitra Bhargava expressed happiness, saying that this land was always under the ownership of the Municipal Corporation, and the court has confirmed this. Plans will soon be made for the development of the land. Some people are preparing to challenge this decision in the High Court, but the Municipal Corporation has already filed a caveat there. Several other officials were also present during the inspection.
